COMMENTS="OpenLDAP server can be started or stopped with the following command:
			sudo /usr/local/etc/init.d/openldap-server start|stop

		The server is started with the default configuration:
		/usr/local/etc/default/openldap-server

		Add these to your backup list (/opt/.filetool.lst) if you modify the files
			usr/local/etc/default/openldap-server
			usr/local/etc/openldap/slapd.conf

		"
